[4.466165, "o", "\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> A WCNF (Weighted CNF) file is available at `/app/test_instance.wcnf`.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> Your task is to:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> 1. Create or use a weighted max SAT solver to solve the max SAT instance at `/app/test_instance.wcnf`\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> 2. Save the optimal objective value to `/app/answer.txt`. For example, if the objective value is 1, run: echo -n \"1\" > answer.txt\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> You may use any programming language and any SAT solver library or implement your own solver.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> '; tmux wait -S done\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
